bobby-dazzler
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a good or amazing person or thing (mainly children's). 1. Anything fine, superior, or outstanding of its kind; ironically, an `eccentric, curious (person)'; corker
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: cf. ruby-dazzler
Pronunciation:
Notes: cf. ruby-dazzler 		1951 14 M 14 St Bede's, Chch 8 BOBBY(-)DAZZLER [something good] -->1951 14 M 10 Wellington H.S. 8 BOBBY DAZZLER [M2] -->1953 14-16 M A17 Thames DHS 8 BOBBY DAZZLER [M4] -->1960 18C F B12 Horowhenua C. 8 BOBBYDAZZLER [NB in ODE as Brit. dated; not in DNZE, correctly]
